      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NIGHTCAPPED (6) goes well for hoop Marshall who has three wins and a placing from seven steers and will be high on confidence following that last-start victory at Ipswich. Can go back-to-back without surprising. The well-related YOSHINO (1) (full to 2xG3 winner and G2 placed Ranier) looked good saluting at the Gold Coast last time out and winning rider Turner sticks in the saddle. Looms as the main danger. OCEAN ZAR (2) has placed two of three over this track and trip and will strip fitter with that first-up effort now in the locker. Top-three credentials. DIVAKARA (5) resumes here but has placed two of three when fresh and can run a race first-up. LA COMETA (3) is a stayer resuming who should be hitting the line with gusto.",
